<title>USA: FTC seeks information from Armstrong.</title>
<headline>FTC seeks information from Armstrong.</headline>
<dateline>LANCASTER, Pa 1997-07-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Armstrong World Industries Inc said Tuesday it had received a request from the U.S. Federal Trade Commission for additional information about its hostile bid for Domco Inc.</p>
<p>Armstrong, which makes furniture, floor coverings and building products, said the request will extend the waiting period until 10 calendar days after it sends the information.</p>
<p>The company is embroiled in a series of court disputes with France's Groupe Sommer Allibert in its effort to buy Domco, a floor covering maker based in Farnham, Quebec.</p>
<p>On July 8, Sommer, a plastics processor which owns 69.2 percent of Domco, said it planned to sue Armstrong for allegedly violating confidentiality agreements between them.</p>
<p>Armstrong has offered C$23 a share for Domco.</p>
